#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set the Controls"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:23
msgid "The mission is to provide quality documentation for the Infinispan community.  But how do you define what that means? What is quality documentation?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:27
msgid "Documentation exists to help you solve problems. And the effectiveness of documentation in helping you do so is generally a good yardstick for measuring quality."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:30
msgid "Over time I've defined what I believe to be the primary criteria for effective technical documentation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:32
msgid "Technically accurate and complete."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:33
msgid "Concise."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:34
msgid "Task-oriented."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Defining the Strategy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:40
msgid "Perhaps the most challenging aspect for working on the Infinispan documentation set is getting into that sweet spot that exists between the bleeding edge and the gardening."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:44
msgid "The bleeding edge is where the action happens. Ideally docs should stay up to date with the code base and go through the same iterations, making improvements with each development cycle."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:49
msgid "Gardening is how I like to think of the maintenance work that docs require.  Much like an actual garden, documentation requires continual upkeep and management to avoid turning into an overgrown, unnavigable jungle of information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:53
msgid "As a team we've been implementing a documentation strategy to overcome these challenges and achieve our mission of delivering quality tech docs. This strategy centers around two things:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "Focusing on the tasks"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:59
msgid "As I mentioned previously, documentation exists to help you solve problems.  Nobody ever sits down and reads the docs like you would a novel. Usually you dip in when you hit a snag or are trying to work out how to do something."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:62
msgid "Procedural content should provide a set of end-to-end steps that help you succeed with your goals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:67
msgid "Documentation that enumerates all available parameters and explains each possible value is great but if it doesn't tell you how to combine parameters in the right way or when to set them, then it's just giving users a long rope to go hang themselves with."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:71
msgid "So hopefully one of the biggest things you'll notice in the Infinispan documentation is that we're adding more procedures. We want to give you the recommended fast path that gets you up and running as quickly as possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "Taking a topic-based approach"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:77
msgid "Topics are logical units of information that can stand alone and map to various information types, of which the three most common are Task, Concept, and Reference."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:81
msgid "One of the benefits of a topic-based writing is that it helps simplify things.  A big obstacle for any kind of writing is just getting a handle on what you need to explain. Technical writers get writer's block too."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:85
msgid "Topic-based writing helps to eliminate that obstacle and take the struggle out of developing content. Start with the task and break things down according to classification and figuring _what_ you need to write becomes much easier."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:89
msgid "At the same time topic-based writing reduces maintenance overhead. A huge win for topics is that they allow reuse. Write something once and use it in different contexts as needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:90
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quick Tour of the Repository Layout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:94
msgid "Now that I've explained some of the motivation, I'd like to briefly delve into how we've organized the docs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:97
msgid "Documentation source lives in link:https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan/tree/master/documentation/src/main/asciidoc[documentation/src/main/asciidoc] and has three main subdirectories:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:99
msgid "link:https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan/tree/master/documentation/src/main/asciidoc/topics[/topics]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:103
msgid "Topics are all the different pieces of information that make up the documentation. Asciidoc files in this directory are prefixed with `proc_*` for procedural content, `con_*` for concepts, and `ref_*` for reference material."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:106
msgid "Apart from the prefixes, topic filenames should be readable and match headings as they appear in the rendered version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:108
msgid "link:https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan/tree/master/documentation/src/main/asciidoc/stories[/stories]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:111
msgid "These are asciidoc files prefixed with `assembly_*` that organize topics into complete, end-to-end sets of content that target specific use cases ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:113
msgid "link:https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan/tree/master/documentation/src/main/asciidoc/titles[/titles]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:116
msgid "These are the main asciidoc files that pull together all the user stories into the titles in the link:https://infinispan.org/documentation/[Infinispan community documentation]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finding the Balance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:122
msgid "We really believe in all the changes we've been making to the docs. It's been exciting to see just how much transformation the doc set has undergone in just over a year (link:https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan/pull/6674[PR 6674])."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:129
msgid "However, given that Infinispan is a community project, we also recognize that these changes have the potential to discourage contributions. Most documentation updates that come from community contributors are small edits or minor updates, usually one or two lines of text. Moving to a topic-based structure adds complexity and creates extra work to make those small changes because you have to sift through many more asciidoc files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:135
msgid "Planning for the new docs strategy was done with core contributors with the goal to preserve and encourage community participation. There have been doc PRs that introduced structural changes that others didn't agreed with. Getting rejected and going back to the drawing board can feel like a setback but ultimately it's about finding the solution where everyone's a winner."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:138
msgid "There is a balance to be had and, like so many things, you find it through conversation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:141
msgid "So, on that note, I'll leave it with a request to join us and keep the conversation going."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2020-03-17-documentation-strategy.adoc:142
msgid "https://issues.jboss.org/projects/ISPN[Report doc bugs (or ask for new content)], https://infinispan.zulipchat.com/[stop by our Zulip room and hang out for a while], or https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/?tagnames=infinispan&sort=newest[ask questions on StackOverflow]."
msgstr ""
